http://www.thehindu.com/news/cities/bangalore/Engineer-suspended-for-causing-loss-to-BBMP/article13981119.ece

An executive engineer has been suspended for causing a loss to the Bruhat Bengaluru Mahanagara Palike (BBMP).According to a press release on Monday, the executive engineer S.V. Rajesh was earlier with the Chikpete division.Fake documentsHe had allegedly cleared bills amounting to Rs. 4.76 crore for asphalting a road to a contractor by creating fake documents and in violation of rules. Investigation later revealed that the contractor had not executed any work. BBMP Commissioner G. Kumar Naik suspended the official, who was working with the road infrastructure department.